news.title: EFC (I)'s net profit increases by 91.71% in Q3 FY25
news.para: EFC (I)'s net consolidated total income stood at Rs 181.50 crore in Q3 FY25, a growth of 4.50 per cent from Rs 173.68 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Infra.Market secures Rs 1,050 crore in pre-IPO funding round
news.para: The round witnessed participation from several prominent investors, including Tiger Global, Evolvence, Foundamental GmbH, Ashish Kacholia, Nikhil Kamath, Abhijit Pai, Sumeet Kanwar, Nuvama and CapriGlobal.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body to propose mandatory structural audits for highrises
news.para: Prior to this, a meeting was called by the Meerut divisional commissioner on Thursday to discuss the agenda. Sources in the GDA said that a compulsory structural audit proposal will be placed before the board.

news.title: Income tax department raids Trehan Group's properties in Alwar
news.para: Presently, the Income Tax team is executing a comprehensive search operation on-site. Nationwide, over 150 personnel from 23 teams have implemented income tax raids at 19 locations of the Trehan Group.

news.title: Adani Infra seeks CCI clearance to acquire majority stake in PSP Projects
news.para: PSP Projects, which has industrial, institutional, residential and luxury projects like the Surat Diamond Bourse, had an order book of Rs 6,546 crore as of September 2024.

news.title: Telangana RERA penalises DLF Gayatri Developers, others over non-compliance
news.para: A complaint was filed by eight individuals, who alleged that the developers marketed plots under the ‘DLF Garden City' project in Nandigama village in Kothur mandal of Rangareddy district without obtaining the required TG RERA registration.

news.title: Austria: Signa's founder arrested on suspicion of hiding assets
news.para: A self-made billionaire, Benko tapped low interest rates to rapidly expand his business, acquiring stakes in prestigious properties from Britain's Selfridges department stores to the Chrysler Building in New York.

news.title: UP-RERA warns builders against misleading project advertisements
news.para: Sanjay Bhoosreddy, chairman, Uttar Pradesh RERA, emphasized that all promotional materials for marketing and sales must adhere to the prescribed guidelines to avoid financial penalties.

news.title: China Vanke in talks to sell logistics firm's stake to GIC: Source
news.para: State-backed Vanke has been trying to sell a number of assets, including its stakes in cold chain logistics firm VX, logistics platform GLP and property management unit Onewo , to ease liquidity pressure, sources said last week.

news.title: London's Workspace reports 1.3% drop in occupancy in Q3 FY25
news.para: Workspace, however, said it had a good start to the New Year with 531 enquires and 337 viewings completed by Jan. 17, including the firm's strongest week for viewings since the pre-pandemic period.

news.title: Bombay HC grants relief to 126 flat buyers in Thane
news.para: The HC held that the change of location of one building among nine in Vasant Lawns was valid and permissible under the Development Control Regulations.

news.title: CBI closes case against DHFL and its directors related to fake home loan accounts
news.para: After over three years of probe, the agency could not find evidence suggesting a criminal conspiracy which could have led to the creation of such accounts, they said.

news.title: Tata Investment Corp acquires office space for Rs 150 crore in Mumbai’s Wadala
news.para: Of this, the company has bought 21,441 sq ft office spread over the entire 17th floor for over Rs 74.24 crore and more than 21,300 sq ft office covering the entire 22nd floor of the commercial tower for nearly Rs 73.76 crore.

news.title: Maharashtra RERA warns developers against unethical practices and misrepresentation
news.para: This follows recent complaints to MahaRERA about developers registering upper-floor flats without a valid Commencement Certificate (CC) and refusing to sign sale agreements despite homebuyers paying over 10% of the total amount.

news.title: UltraTech Cement's net profit dips 16.98% in Q3 FY25
news.para: UltraTech Cement's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 17,437.62 crore in Q3 FY25, a growth of 3.30 per cent from Rs 16,880.45 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Coimbatore civic body's struggles to meet its property tax collection target
news.para: Last fiscal, the corporation had managed to collect 92% of the property tax collection target. Having achieved just 47 of the target so far and with just two months remaining in the financial year, even achieving the same feat is a daunting task this time.

news.title: Mahindra Lifespaces acquires 8.2 acre land in Bengaluru
news.para: Mahindra Lifespace Developers' land has a developable potential of approximately 0.9 million sq ft of saleable area and a projected gross development value (GDV) of almost Rs 1,000 crore.

news.title: BMRCL initiates land acquisition process for Namma metro phase 3
news.para: Initially, 26,811 square meters of land were acquired for the stretch from JP Nagar Phase 4 to Mysuru Road Metro Station.

news.title: Housing allotted to tribals in PVTG villages to be completed by March 2026: ASR collector
news.para: Through a power point presentation, the collector elaborated about the implementation of the scheme in the district, explaining the challenges faced in construction and the steps being taken to overcome them.

news.title: Haryana govt proposes policy allowing tree felling on urban land allotted for projects
news.para: The policy is proposed to supersede all previous orders related to tree felling outside of forests, even if those areas are notified under Section 3 of the Punjab Land Preservation Act (PLPA), 1900
